title: Kim Kardashian posts clip of 1988 debut in Barbie magazine | Daily Mail Online
text: 293 shares 'Look at what a star reading Star Maps,' Kim narrated. She also was shown at Universal Studios in the special California issue near a banner reading I Love L.A. Reality star: The Keeping Up With The Kardashians star, shown earlier this month in West Hollywood, California, posted her 1988 Barbie magazine spread on Snapchat Special issue: Kim was featured in a special California issue of Barbie magazine Disney girl: The reality star wore Mickey Mouse ears while kneeling next to Mickey's star on the Hollywood Walk of Fame Star maps: Kim was shown perusing Star Maps with other girls in the magazine 'Look. I Love L.A., how cute,' Kim said in the video. The Keeping Up With The Kardashians star also posted a Snapchat video of herself having fun with filters. She proclaimed her love for the butterfly filter and also endorsed the 'original flower crown' filter. Studio tour: The magazine spread included a trip to Universal Studios Loving it: Kim noted the I Love L.A. banner in the magazine Celebrity obsession: The youngster showed an early interest in celebrities in the photos Cool kids: Kim wore sunglasses at the iconic Chinese Theatre in Hollywood 'Yeah, that's special,' Kim said while admiring herself in the clip. Kim rose to fame in 2007 when a sex tape with former boyfriend Ray J was leaked and Keeping Up With The Kardashians premiered on the E! network. She's been married since 2014 to rapper Kanye West, 39, and they have three-year-old daughter North and one-year-old son Saint together. Filter fun: The mother of two posted Snapchat videos of herself having fun with filters That's special: Kim used the flower crown filter and said it was 'special' Share or comment on this article 293
